The paper deals with training deep neural networks on large-scale web images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of text queries to crawl images, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of noisy labels and data imbalance, which are common challenges in multimedia analysis (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
